    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All seven assessed credibility factors meet or exceed required levels for MRL 2. Six factors appropriately scoped as not-assessed per ASME V&V 40 Table 4 guidance for MRL 2 Class II devices. NIH predictions agree with experimental data within combined uncertainty at all five operating points. RH < 1 criterion satisfied, supporting the regulatory claim that the CFD model reliably identifies worst-case hemolysis operating conditions. The UQ campaign (Sobol sensitivity analysis, summarized in Validation Report Appendix C) confirms rotational speed as the dominant hemolysis driver and demonstrates robustness to geometric manufacturing variation. Assessment team unanimously recommends acceptance of the credibility evidence package.",
